what dentistary

Dentistry is the branch of medicine that focuses on the diagnosis, prevention, and treatment of conditions and diseases affecting the teeth, gums, and mouth. Dentists are healthcare professionals who specialize in providing oral care to patients of all ages, including performing cleanings, fillings, extractions, and other treatments to maintain or restore oral health. Dentistry also includes cosmetic procedures such as teeth whitening, veneers, and orthodontic treatments like braces or Invisalign. Regular dental check-ups are essential for maintaining good oral health and preventing dental problems from developing.
